ken.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>By Road</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba National Park is well-connected by road to nearby cities and towns. <strong>Bus services are available </strong>from major cities like Nagpur, Pune, Mumbai, Bangalore, Bhopal, and many more to nearby towns like Chandrapur and Chimur. These buses may be operated by state transport authorities or private companies. It\'s advisable to check the bus schedule and book your tickets in advance, especially during peak seasons. From Chandrapur or Chimur, you can take local transport options such as taxis, auto-rickshaws, or shared jeeps to reach Tadoba National Park.  It usually takes 30 to 45 minutes by road to reach the park.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Local Transport</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once you reach the area of Tadoba National Park, you can hire <strong>local taxis, jeeps, or auto-rickshaws </strong>to reach your accommodation or directly to the park entrance gates. Many resorts and lodges near the park offer pick-up and drop-off services for their guests.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It\'s advisable to plan your transportation and consider factors such as distance, travel time, entry timings, safari schedules, and convenience when choosing the best option to reach the Park. There are three main entry points to the Park: <strong>Moharli Gate, Kolara Gate, and Navegaon Gate.</strong> Choose your accommodation and travel options according to the entry gate you have chosen for your safari. Additionally, always check for the latest travel updates and road conditions before starting your journey towards <strong><a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/\">Tadoba National Park.</a></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Published by&nbsp;Sanskriti Goyal on&nbsp;February 9, 2024</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','How to Reach Tadoba National Park','','inherit','closed','closed','','12614-revision-v1','','','2024-02-13 07:08:44','2024-02-13 07:08:44','',12614,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12658',0,'revision','',0),(12660,4,'2024-02-13 07:19:54','2024-02-13 07:19:54','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In Tadoba National Park, there are several safari gates from which visitors can enter for wildlife sightings. These gates include <strong>6 gates from the core zone and 12 gates from the buffer zone</strong>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Gates of Tadoba National Park</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The core zone is a protected area where the natural resources and wildlife are highly conserved. In this area human activity is minimal. <strong>Core zone gates are Moharli Gate, Kolara Gate, Navegaon Gate, Pangdi Gate,  Zari Gate and Khutwanda Gate.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The buffer zone, on the other hand, is the area which is surrounding the core zone. Conservation efforts take place in this area but limited human activity is allowed here. Buffer zone gates are Agarzari, Adegaon Dewada, Junona, Kolara, Ramdegi-Navegaon, Alizanza, Madnapur, Mamla, Pangdi, Sirkada, Zari/Peth, Kessalghat, Chora Chinchola and Nimdela – Ramdegi.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Zones of Tadoba National Park</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are four zones in Tadoba National Park that can be accessed through different gates.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>1. <strong>Moharli Zone:</strong> For a safari ride in this zone you can enter through the Moharli and Khutwanda gates of the Core zone and the Devada, Adegao, Agarzari, Junona &amp; Mamla gates of the Buffer zone.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>2. <strong>Kolara Zone</strong>: To enter this zone you have to book the safari from the Kolara gate of the core zone. You can also enter this zone from Alizanza, Madnapur, Sirkada, Kolara Chauradeo, Palasgaon, and Belara gates of the Buffer zone.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>3. <strong>Navegaon Zone</strong>: This zone can be accessed through the Navegaon gate of the core zone. Buffer zone gates to enter this zone are Navegaon Ramdegi &amp; Nimdela gate.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>4. <strong>Pangadi and Zari zone</strong>: 2 core gates have been made to enter this zone, Pangadi &amp; Zari Gate. You can also book a safari from Pangadi Aswal Chuha, Keslaghat &amp; Zari Peth gate of the buffer zone.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Best Gate of Tadoba National Park</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Although all the gates of Tadoba offer unique landscapes and wildlife viewing opportunities, the Moharli zone is considered the most popular zone for safari due to its higher chance of spotting tigers and other wildlife.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>The most popular gate for safari in Tadoba National Park is the Moharli gate.</strong> This gate is famous among tourists because the black leopard has been frequently spotted here. You can find various accommodation options near this gate. This gate is closest to Telia Lake, many wild animals can be spotted at this lake as they come here to quench their thirst. Moharli has a dense forest area, making it a prime habitat for animals like tigers. So if you\'re looking for the best chance to see wild animals along with tigers in Tadoba, Moharli Gate is the way to go. What are you waiting for? Book your safari now from <a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/tadoba-safari-booking