important stuff that you should take for a safari ride in this park.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>1. ID and Permits -</strong> Permits are written permissions given by authorities in the form of tickets to enter the park. The timings, zone, guest information, etc are written on them. These are required at the entry gate, you cannot enter the park premises without permits. IDs are your identity cards, you have to bring the same IDs about which you have filled in information while taking the permit. It can be a Passport, Voter ID, License, Aadhar&nbsp; Card, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>2. Wear Comfortable Clothes </strong>- If you’re going in summer then it is advised that you should pack lightweight comfortable clothes, it would be best if they have full sleeves so that you can protect yourself from insect bites and sun damage. If you’re coming in winter then choose layering clothing style. Pack your jackets or sweaters for morning and evening rides.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>3. Footwear-</strong> Try to wear comfortable boots or sneakers, ladies keep your heels at home. If you want a comfortable journey without breaking your precious footwear then choose hiking boots over anything.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>4. Hat or Shades -</strong> The temperature is hot and humid during summer in the park, so don’t forget to bring your hat and sunglasses so that you can protect your eyes and face from the sun and it will also give you a nice sighting experience during Jungle Safari.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>5. Keep these</strong> Things Handy - Binoculars are important for sighting animals so that you can see them from a distance, of course, you can find some animals around you but the more sighting the better, right? Cameras are important for taking nice photographs of animals and birds while they are living in their homes.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>6. Protect Yourself -</strong> You should definitely take bug spray and sunscreens with you so that you can protect your skin from bugs and insects of Tadoba-Andhari Tiger Reserve. Sunscreen is important for protection from harmful UV rays, do re-apply it every two hours.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>7. Important Backpack&nbsp;</strong> - Take a backpack in which you can put above mentioned things along with water, snacks, a first aid kit, and any medicine that you’re taking for your health concerns. Try to carry a smaller backpack so that you can enjoy the safari ride.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>8. Power -</strong> Don’t forget to keep your chargers, power backup, and extra batteries with you for your electronic devices like phones and cameras so that you can take some good shots.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Conclusion</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After taking all this stuff, you’re ready to go on a thrilling journey to Tadoba National Park, to book your permits you can visit <a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/\">Tadoba National Park Online Booking</a> and you can gain more information about the park there.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Published by&nbsp;Sanskriti Goyal </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Pack Smart for Tadoba National Park','','publish','open','open','','pack-smart-for-tadoba-national-park','','','2024-04-10 08:26:02','2024-04-10 08:26:02','',0,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12711',0,'post','',0),(12712,4,'2024-04-05 10:38:22','2024-04-05 10:38:22','Pack Smart for Tadoba National Park ','Pack Smart for Tadoba National Park','Pack Smart for Tadoba National Park ','inherit','open','closed','','pexels-photo-9186183','','',