-heading\"><strong>Mammals of Tadoba</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can spot various types of Mammal in Tadoba like Jungle cats, Sloth bears, Nilgai, Indian Leopard, Barking deer, chital, gaur, sambar, striped hyena, spotted deer, dhole, small Indian civet, porcupines, fox, rhesus macaque, leopard cat, blue bull, honey badger, chausinga, common langurs, Indian pangolins, wild boar, flying squirrel, chinkara, wolf, jackal, and rusty-spotted cat with many more.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Reptiles of Tadoba</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba National Park is home to several Reptiles like Russell\'s Viper, Terrapins, Indian Cobra, Indian python, different Snakes, Common Indian monitor, Krait, Indian Star tortoise, and Marsh crocodile which can be found in lakes or watering holes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Birds of Tadoba</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba is a paradise for Bird watchers and photographers, <strong>more than 195 species of birds</strong> can be found here which includes water birds and raptors like the Crested serpent eagle, warblers, Stone curlew, Orange-Headed Thrush, Black-naped blue flycatcher, Crested Treeswift, Crested Honey Buzzard, Grey-headed fish eagle, Changeable hawk-eagle, Asian Paradise flycatcher, Bronze-Winged Jacana, Lesser Golden-backed Woodpecker, Indian pitta, peacock, shy jungle fowl, Indian scimitar babbler, painted Francolin, Tickell’s blue flycatcher, Bonelli’s eagle, pipits, Malabar pied hornbill, golden oriole, plum headed parakeet, Gray jungle fowl, mottled wood owl, brown fish owl, drongos, larks, and Munias with many more.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Insects of Tadoba</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba National Park is a dense forest in which many types of insects are found such as Monarch, Pansies, Mormons, Swordtails, danaid egg fly, great egg fly, praying mantis, stick insects, dragonflies, Jewel beetles, giant wood spiders, signature spiders, redwood spiders, like lynx spiders, crab spiders and wolf spiders with many more. One thing to keep in mind is that you must have a guide with you so that you can spot these insects.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Remember, when visiting Tadoba or any national park, it\'s important to <strong>respect the animals and their habitat to ensure their conservation and safet</strong>y. Click on <strong><a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/tadoba-safari-booking\">Tadoba Safari Booking</a></strong> to observe this wide range of Fauna in Tadoba National Park.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Published by Sanskriti Goyal </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Fauna of Tadoba National Park','','inherit','closed','closed','','12592-revision-v1','','','2024-04-06 04:47:47','2024-04-06 04:47:47','',12592,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12716',0,'revision','',0),(12717,4,'2024-04-06 04:48:24','2024-04-06 04:48:24','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With rich biodiversity and a huge number of tigers, Tadoba National Park is a famous wildlife sanctuary among enthusiasts and nature lovers. To enjoy your rides to the fullest without worrying about safety you have to follow certain rules that will ensure proper safety of humans as well as animals.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">Tadoba National Park</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba National Park is a wild location in Chandrapur district, also known as the biological hotspot of Maharashtra. Apart from tigers, this park is home to leopards, wild pigs, sambar, chital and wild dogs, sloth bears, and a variety of species of birds. Along with these animals, you can find many bamboo and teak trees with other flora species. A safari ride in this park will surely be an amazing experience. This park should be on the visit list of people coming to Maharashtra to spend their holidays. To gain more information and book a safari ride in this amazing park you can visit <strong><a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/\">Tadoba National Park Online Booking</a>.</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Do’s in Tadoba&nbsp;</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>When you book your rides then permits will be given to you to enter the park, do take them with you. Without permits, entry is not allowed in the park.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You should always maintain a safe distance from animals and avoid disturbing them while on your safari.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You should observe the park quietly without making any noise.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You should always follow your guide\'s instructions as they know the park better than you.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>&nbsp;There are designated routes for safaris and nature walks inside the park so you have to enjoy there only.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>&nbsp;Always respect the park’s boundaries and avoid straying into restricted areas.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>If you want to see animals from a closer view, use binoculars or cameras, instead of approaching them.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Try to talk in a lower voice when having a conversation with someone.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Carry a plastic bag to keep your garbage, and then throw it after coming outside in the dustbin.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Read all the rules and regulations before entering the park.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Don\'ts in Tadoba&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Don’t try to feed animals as it will disturb their natural habitat and they will start depending on humans.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Don’t feed animals because of safety reasons also.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>If you find any animal cute, don’t try to touch it, as it can be wild.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Don’t use recorders or any sounds inside the park as animals get disturbed by them.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Don’t use flash photography, especially when photographing animals at night.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Smoking and lighting fires are strictly prohibited inside the park.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Don’t pluck flowers or don’t try to take anything from the park as it will disturb the natural life.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Don’t take alcohol inside, as it is strictly prohibited.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Talking non-veg inside the park is not allowed.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Don’t try to get down from the jeep, unless told by your guide.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Conclusion By following these rules and regulations you can have a fun time in Tadoba. If you adhere to these simple do’s and don’ts then surely your safari ride will be thrilling and adventurous in Tadoba National Park. To make your trip more memorable you can choose from our<a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/tadoba-tour-packages\"> tour packages of Tadoba</a> that will allow you to enjoy the best in less time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Published by Sanskriti Goyal </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Essential Do\'s and Don\'ts in Tadoba National Park','With rich biodiversity and a huge number of tigers, Tadoba National Park is a famous wildlife sanctuary among enthusiasts and nature lovers. ','inherit','closed','closed','','12709-revision-v1','','','2024-04-06 04:48:24','2024-04-06 04:48:24','',12709,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12717',0,'revision','',0),(12718,4,'2024-04-06 04:50:21','2024-04-06 04:50:21','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/\">Tadoba National Park</a> which is a wild palace, famous among tourists, especially wildlife enthusiasts, remains closed during the monsoon season because of rainfall. After summer, monsoon takes place from July to mid-October and in that period, tourism activities shut down in the area, but this place becomes live during this time. During monsoon, with shades of green, this jungle becomes alive with a mesmerizing symphony of life. The monsoon season is a scenic time, which brings great transformation in the park after summer, as the rain brings out the beauty of greenery in the area. This time is breeding time for some animals and people cannot disturb them during this season. The park becomes brown and dry because of the heat in summer, but because of the monsoon, it changes to a scenic place for tourism in the upcoming months. Everyone must visit here during this time of the year.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">The Greenery Unfolds</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As the rain drops gently touch the dusty grounds, a miracle happens. From a dry land to a lush green forest, the park transforms completely. The dull land becomes a lively paradise with greenery and beautiful flowering plants. Trees grow tall which makes a beautiful roof of leaves that provides shelter to animals living there. Many herbivore animals find food in this new green world. Everything looks bright, and the air smells fresh and new.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">Wildlife Becomes Happy&nbsp;</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Because of lush green lands, animals start moving. Grazers, like deer, become happy because they get plenty of grass to munch. Big bison called gaur move around like strong castles. Monkeys, like langurs and macaques play around on tall trees, which shows how flora and fauna are connected. Butterflies and other insects sip nectar from flowers and juice from fruits. It’s like a beautiful transformation in nature that people get to see working there.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">The King Comes Out&nbsp;</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With plenty of new plants and food roaming around (prey animals), the real king of the park appears. During monsoon, many prey animals roam in parks for munching and tigers catch them with their amazing skills. As the rain fills up the waterholes, the tigers come out of their hidden homes to drink and show who\'s boss. Their shiny fur covered in raindrops makes them even more mysterious and impressive. With so much greenery around, the tigers can hunt easily and they get more energetic during this time.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">It\'s time for safaris</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When the rainy clouds go away, the Safari season starts in October, and it\'s a big deal. During the early month after the monsoon (from October to December), people who love animals and photographers from everywhere come to see this amazing sight. The park remains lush green with beautiful flowers. Animals are more energetic with plenty of food and migratory birds also visit during winters. Every wildlife enthusiast and nature lover becomes excited, and the safari spots fill up very quickly for rides. Many people pre-book their safaris during monsoons so that they can experience the beauty and wilderness just after the opening of the park. If you want to go, you can book your spot quickly online from Tadoba National Park Online Booking. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Published by Sanskriti Goyal </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Monsoon Beauty of Tadoba National Park','The park becomes brown and dry because of the heat in summer, but because of the monsoon, it changes to a scenic place for tourism in the upcoming months. Everyone must visit here during this time of the year. ','inherit','closed','closed','','12705-revision-v1','','','2024-04-06 04:50:21','2024-04-06 04:50:21','',12705,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12718',0,'revision','',0),(12719,4,'2024-04-06 04:50:52','2024-04-06 04:50:52','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba Andhari Tiger Reserve or <a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/\">Tadoba National Park</a> is a wild tourist spot, famous among wildlife enthusiasts and nature lovers. This park is located in Maharashtra and is one of the most preferred tiger destinations in India. Here you can enjoy different types of activities like jeep safaris, boat rides, birding, trekking, etc. Here is a list of activities that you can enjoy in and around Tadoba National Park.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":12702,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://tadobapark.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Top-Activities-Around-Tadoba-National-Park-Inner-Image-1024x538.jpg\" alt=\"Top Activities Around Tadoba\" class=\"wp-image-12702\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">1. Visit to Butterfly Garden&nbsp;</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The beautiful butterfly garden is located at the Agarzari village on Chandrapur- Moharli Road near Tadoba National Park. This garden covers a huge area of five acres and it’s a real butterfly world. The butterfly goes through 4 different life stages: egg, larva, Chrysalis, and adult, you can see each life stage of butterflies here. It’s an open-air meadow that has food plants to attract butterflies. Many butterflies from Tadoba visit this place and around 80 species of them, call this place their home. This garden was inaugurated back on February 10th and it was made to educate tourists about butterflies and the importance of every species in the ecosystem. You can get knowledge about different kinds of butterflies after coming here. This garden was made to conserve butterflies but many people try to catch butterflies in their hands, and because of that, a glasshouse is there in the garden to help the visitors watch the butterflies in proximity.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">2. Boat ride in Irai Lake&nbsp;</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Forest Department offers a boat riding facility on the backwaters of Irai Lake. Many bird watchers and photographers like to do this activity as many residents as well as migratory birds can be found near the lake. Birds like heaven Crested Pochard, Grey Heron, Stork Billed Kingfisher, Cotton pygmy goose, etc. can be found with different migratory birds during the winter season. You can enjoy boat riding on Irai Lake from 7:00 AM – 5:00 PM. Just like safari rides, boating is also closed for tourist activity in Tadoba from July to October end because of the monsoon season. Visiting here and doing a boat ride will surely be an amazing experience for Birdwatchers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">3. Try Jeep Safari Ride&nbsp;</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba National Park is a wild place that is famous for its tiger population along with a wide variety of other fauna and flora species. Every year, thousands of people come here to see animals from a closer view. People can do that by going on jeep safari rides. Jeep safari rides are done on gypsies, that go inside the park, it offers chances to see wild animals in their natural habitat. To go on rides inside the park, you have to get permits from forest officials. You can book your permit from <a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/tadoba-safari-booking\">Tadoba Online Safari Booking</a>. These rides are done in different zones of the park at different times so that people can explore the area according to their preferences. People sometimes cannot book rides according to their timing or zone preference because the slots tend to fill up quickly, so it is advised to book them 45 days before your arrival.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">4. Walk into Local Villages</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After a thrilling safari ride in Tadoba, walk towards villages near the park. This park is surrounded by various Gond Tribal villages and you can interact with people, to learn about their culture and beliefs. Tell them about yours and gain knowledge about them. You can spend your time enjoying traditional dance and music performances. Take time to see their handicrafts that are uniquely made. Try local food from the shops in and around the villages. This sharing of culture will help you understand how people and nature are linked.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">5. Ramdegi Waterfalls and Temple&nbsp;</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you’re a devotee and into spirituality, then you must visit Ramdegi Temple. It can be a good break from the busy, city life. You can find peace and calm in the surroundings of this place. If you want to have some fun, click some good pictures, and want to see different types of fishes, birds, and butterflies then a visit to Ramdegi waterfall should be there on your checklist. It’s a beautiful scenic place that is located close to Tadoba National Park.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Published by Sanskriti Goyal </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Top Activities Around Tadoba National Park','Tadoba Andhari Tiger Reserve or Tadoba National Park is a wild tourist spot, famous among wildlife enthusiasts and nature lovers. This park is located in Maharashtra and is one of the most preferred tiger destinations in India','inherit','closed','closed','','12701-revision-v1','','','2024-04-06 04:50:52','2024-04-06 04:50:52','',12701,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12719',0,'revision','',0),(12720,4,'2024-04-06 04:52:04','2024-04-06 04:52:04','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba National Park is a beautiful place in India where many wild animals live freely in their natural habitat. One of the most exciting animals you can find there is the tiger. Tigers are big cats with orange fur and black stripes. They are very strong and can run very fast.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In Tadoba, tigers are the kings and queens of the jungle. They roam around freely, hunting for food and taking care of their families. Seeing a tiger in the wild is a thrilling experience that many people dream about. Tigers in <strong><a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/\">Tadoba National Park</a></strong> are known for their unique behaviors. They have territories that they mark with their scent to show other tigers that it\'s their area. Male tigers are especially protective of their territory and will defend it from other males.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>These majestic creatures are not only beautiful but also important for the ecosystem. They help control the population of other animals like deer and wild boar, which keeps the balance of nature in check.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba National Park is dedicated to protecting tigers and their habitat. The authorities of the park work very hard to make sure that the tigers are safe from poachers and other dangers. They also educate visitors about the importance of conserving these magnificent animals.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you ever visit Tadoba National Park, keep your eyes peeled for these incredible tigers. But remember, they are wild animals, so it\'s important to respect their space and observe them from a safe distance. Enjoy the beauty of nature and the thrill of seeing these majestic creatures in their natural habitat. You can do <strong><a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/tadoba-safari-booking\">tadoba online booking</a> </strong>for a thrilling safari ride in the park.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Published by&nbsp;Sanskriti Goyal</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Majestic Tigers of Tadoba National Park','','inherit','closed','closed','','12678-revision-v1','','','2024-04-06 04:52:04','2024-04-06 04:52:04','',12678,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12720',0,'revision','',0),(12721,4,'2024-04-06 04:52:34','2024-04-06 04:52:34','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here are some essential tips that you should follow for a thrilling and memorable safari ride at <strong>Tadoba National Park</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>1. Wear light-colored, comfy clothes that are loose-fitting. Don\'t wear bright colors because they might attract animals and bugs. Try to wear something in brown or green color so that it blends in nature. Also, wear closed-toe shoes that are good for walking</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>2. Don’t forget to carry a backpack with you. Put in it important things like sunscreen, sunglasses, bug spray, a hat, a camera, a power bank, and binoculars. Bring enough water and some snacks to keep yourself hydrated and energetic during the safari.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>3. Remember, you might not see animals right away. It\'s important to be patient and enjoy being in nature. Always remind yourself that you’re not just here for animals, but to experience nature also.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>4. The park has some rules and regulations for your safety and the safety of the animals. Listen to your guide and do what they say.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>5. Animals in <strong><a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/\">Tadoba National Park</a></strong> are wild and can be unpredictable. Stay a safe distance away from them, and don\'t make loud noises or sudden movements. Don\'t try to feed or get close to them, and don\'t litter in the park.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>6. Tadoba National Park is a special place that needs to be taken care of. Don\'t pick flowers, break branches, or hurt plants and animals. Leave the park the way you found it, without causing any harm.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>7. Don’t forget to bring your permit and original ID, for a smooth entry.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>8. It is advised to book your safari 2 days before your trip. Experience hassle-free <strong>Tadoba Online Booking</strong> with our user-friendly platform.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Published by&nbsp;Sanskriti Goyal </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Essential Tips for Tadoba National Park Safari','','inherit','closed','closed','','12676-revision-v1','','','2024-04-06 04:52:34','2024-04-06 04:52:34','',12676,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12721',0,'revision','',0),(12722,4,'2024-04-06 04:52:56','2024-04-06 04:52:56','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba National Park is in India. It\'s a big place for animals to live in their natural habitat. Here are some facts about Tadoba National Park</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>1. Tadoba National Park is one of the biggest national parks of India. It’s a beautiful place in India where many animals can be found. It is located in the Chandrapur district of Maharashtra, India. Tadoba is one of the oldest and largest national parks in Maharashtra. It is named after Tadoba Lake, which is in the middle of the park</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>2. This park is home to different types of fauna species, but the most famous ones are tigers. Tadoba is known for having a good number of tigers. People from all over the world come to see these majestic creatures in their natural habitat. Apart from tigers, there are also leopards, sloth bears, wild dogs, hyenas, and many types of deer and birds. It is one of the best places to see wild animals in their natural habitat.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>3. <strong>Tadoba National Park</strong> is pretty big, covering over 600 square kilometers of land and it is filled with forests, grasslands, and water bodies. It\'s a great place for wildlife enthusiasts and photographers to spend their time. There are many safari options available for visitors to explore the park and see the animals up close. These safaris are usually guided by knowledgeable people who know a lot about the park and its wildlife. You can do <strong><a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/tadoba-safari-booking\">Tadoba Safari Booking</a></strong> from our website.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>4. Talking about the history of this park, it has a rich history as it was once a hunting ground for the Gond kings of Central India. Then it became a protected area to conserve wildlife. The park is managed by the Forest Department of Maharashtra.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>5. Not only animals but one can find a lot of flora species here which includes thick forests, trees, shrubs, herbs, and other plants. Some of the common trees found here include teak, bamboo, mahua, and tendu.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>6. The best time to visit Tadoba National Park is between March to May. During this time, animals come near water bodies in search of water. This is the best time for animal sightings. However, if you’re a bird watcher then the best time to visit would be between November to February, during this time you can spot resident birds as well as migratory birds. The park remains closed during the monsoon season, from June to September, because the heavy rains make it difficult to travel and it is also breeding time for animals.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>7. To get entry into Tadoba National Park, visitors need to get permits from the park authorities. These permits can be obtained online or from the park\'s entrance gate. Make sure to bring your permit and original ID card during your visit, failing which you cannot enter the park premises. After your safari you can stay near the park, <strong><a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/hotels-in-tadoba\">Tadoba Hotel Booking</a></strong> can be done on our website.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>8.Tadoba is a protected area and just like many wildlife sanctuaries,&nbsp; Tadoba faces challenges like habitat loss and conflicts between animals and people.&nbsp; The government takes care of this park and they always make conservation efforts to protect the park and its inhabitants.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Overall,this Park is a wonderful place to experience nature and see a wide variety of wildlife. It offers a unique opportunity to observe animals in their natural habitat and learn about conservation efforts in India. Whether you\'re a nature lover, a wildlife enthusiast, a bird watcher or just looking for a peaceful getaway, <strong>Tadoba National Park</strong> has something for everyone.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Published by&nbsp;Sanskriti Goyal</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Facts About Tadoba National Park','','inherit','closed','closed','','12673-revision-v1','','','2024-04-06 04:52:56','2024-04-06 04:52:56','',12673,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12722',0,'revision','',0),(12723,4,'2024-04-06 04:53:40','2024-04-06 04:53:40','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https://tadobapark.com/\"><strong>Tadoba National Park</strong></a> is not only famous for its royal Bengal tigers but also for its fascinating birdlife. It covers a big area of 625 sq. km. and is a paradise for bird enthusiasts. Whether you\'re near the lake or exploring other parts of the park, you will surely be mesmerized by the varied range of bird species here. There is a&nbsp; river inside the park named Andhari, this river provides a habitat for a wide variety of water birds and raptors. From big raptors like the Crested Serpent Eagle and Changeable Hawk Eagles to water birds there is a lot to see here.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:para