/a> in Tadoba National Park are the best options for exploring the park. While on your safari rides, you can enjoy spotting the Royal Bengal Tiger, or Indian Leopard, Barking deer, small Indian civet, flying squirrel, fox, jackal, wolf, etc., and the flora species such as Bija tree, Kusum tree, bark tree, bamboo groves, and grasses and so on. If you especially want a tiger sighting experience then book your ride for the Moharli zone as that one is famous among wildlife enthusiasts for prominent tiger sightings.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"20px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:20px\">2. Safari At Night</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This safari has recently been added to Tadoba National Park. Now, you can experience the thrill of the Jungle at Night. This safari is more popular than day safari among wildlife enthusiasts as it offers more thrill. During your safari, you don\'t know which animal can come in front of your jeep out of the blue at night. These safaris are best for experiencing the adventure of being inside a jungle at night. Many animals get active, especially during the night so it\'s the best time to spot those animals.&nbsp; These safaris are action-packed as during your safari you can listen to the wild sounds of animals but you won’t be able to see them from a distance.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"20px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:20px\">3. Machan Watch</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This one is the latest tourist attraction in Tadoba Andheri Tiger Reserve. Machan watch is opened in the Moharli and Palasgaon buffer areas. People can go up by climbing and sit in these machans to spot wild animals from the top. The safaris that you have booked will take you on these machans. Two people can climb on machan with one guide at a time to enjoy panoramic views with better sighting. People can carry their refreshments at the top but littering is not allowed so keep a plastic bag for disposing of your waste in it so that after the ride you can throw the plastic bag in the dustbin.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"20px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:20px\">4. Village Visits</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can go for nature walks in the buffer zones of Tadoba. There are many villages in the buffer zones of Tadoba Andhari Tiger Reserve and you can visit these areas. These villages are occupied by tribal groups of Gonds, Korkur, Kolams, and Andh, and you can spend time with them, and chat with them with help from a guide. People can go to their work areas and see nice bamboo works of furniture, home decor, baskets, swings, etc. that artisans and craftsmen make.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"20px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:20px\">5. Sevagram</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is a town where Gandhi Ji (father of the nation) has set up an ashram, and he also lived here. This ashram is located at a 2 hours drive from Tadoba National Park and Gandhi Ji lived here from <strong>1936</strong> to his <strong>death in 1948</strong>. You can find artifacts of India’s freedom struggles in this museum. A trip to Sevagram will give you a glimpse of the memories of pre-independent India.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Unforgettable Moments at Tadoba National Park','Tadoba National Park is a nice tourist destination that has many things to offer. This place has recently become one of the most preferred destinations in India. ','inherit','closed','closed','','12727-revision-v1','','','2024-04-09 04:48:28','2024-04-09 04:48:28','',12727,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12734',0,'revision','',0),(12738,4,'2024-04-10 07:05:55','2024-04-10 07:05:55','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba National Park is one of the biggest National Parks of India. It covers an area of 625 sq. km.&nbsp; It is one of the best places to observe the <strong>Royal Bengal Tiger</strong> in its natural habitat. Not only Royal Bengal Tigers but Tadoba National Park is filled with various fauna species like Hyenas, spotted deer, wild boars, barking deer, Gray languor, Leopard, leopard cat, Jungle cat, Wild dog, Jackal, Russell\'s Viper, Terrapins, Indian Cobra, Orange-Headed Thrush, Black-naped blue flycatcher, Crested Treeswift, danaid egg fly, great egg fly, Mormons and Swordtails with many others. Let’s explore the fauna of <strong><a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/\">Tadoba National Park </a></strong>in detail:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Mammals of Tadoba</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can spot various types of Mammal in Tadoba like Jungle cats, Sloth bears, Nilgai, Indian Leopard, Barking deer, chital, gaur, sambar, striped hyena, spotted deer, dhole, small Indian civet, porcupines, fox, rhesus macaque, leopard cat, blue bull, honey badger, chausinga, common langurs, Indian pangolins, wild boar, flying squirrel, chinkara, wolf, jackal, and rusty-spotted cat with many more.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Reptiles of Tadoba</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba National Park is home to several Reptiles like Russell\'s Viper, Terrapins, Indian Cobra, Indian python, different Snakes, Common Indian monitor, Krait, Indian Star tortoise, and Marsh crocodile which can be found in lakes or watering holes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Birds of Tadoba</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba is a paradise for Bird watchers and photographers, <strong>more than 195 species of birds</strong> can be found here which includes water birds and raptors like the Crested serpent eagle, warblers, Stone curlew, Orange-Headed Thrush, Black-naped blue flycatcher, Crested Treeswift, Crested Honey Buzzard, Grey-headed fish eagle, Changeable hawk-eagle, Asian Paradise flycatcher, Bronze-Winged Jacana, Lesser Golden-backed Woodpecker, Indian pitta, peacock, shy jungle fowl, Indian scimitar babbler, painted Francolin, Tickell’s blue flycatcher, Bonelli’s eagle, pipits, Malabar pied hornbill, golden oriole, plum headed parakeet, Gray jungle fowl, mottled wood owl, brown fish owl, drongos, larks, and Munias with many more.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Insects of Tadoba</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba National Park is a dense forest in which many types of insects are found such as Monarch, Pansies, Mormons, Swordtails, danaid egg fly, great egg fly, praying mantis, stick insects, dragonflies, Jewel beetles, giant wood spiders, signature spiders, redwood spiders, like lynx spiders, crab spiders and wolf spiders with many more. One thing to keep in mind is that you must have a guide with you so that you can spot these insects.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Remember, when visiting Tadoba or any national park, it\'s important to <strong>respect the animals and their habitat to ensure their conservation and safet</strong>y. Click on <strong><a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/tadoba-safari-booking\">Tadoba Safari Booking</a></strong> to observe this wide range of Fauna in Tadoba National Park.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Published by&nbsp;Sanskriti Goyal </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Fauna of Tadoba National Park','Tadoba National Park is one of the biggest National Parks of India. It covers an area of 625 sq. km.  It is one of the best places to observe the Royal Bengal Tiger in its natural habitat. ','inherit','closed','closed','','12592-revision-v1','','','2024-04-10 07:05:55','2024-04-10 07:05:55','',12592,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12738',0,'revision','',0),(12740,4,'2024-04-10 07:10:28','2024-04-10 07:10:28','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In Tadoba National Park, there are several safari gates from which visitors can enter for wildlife sightings. These gates include <strong>6 gates from the core zone and 12 gates from the buffer zone</strong>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Gates of Tadoba National Park</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The core zone is a protected area where the natural resources and wildlife are highly conserved. In this area human activity is minimal. <strong>Core zone gates are Moharli Gate, Kolara Gate, Navegaon Gate, Pangdi Gate,&nbsp; Zari Gate and Khutwanda Gate.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The buffer zone, on the other hand, is the area which is surrounding the core zone. Conservation efforts take place in this area but limited human activity is allowed here. Buffer zone gates are Agarzari, Adegaon Dewada, Junona, Kolara, Ramdegi-Navegaon, Alizanza, Madnapur, Mamla, Pangdi, Sirkada, Zari/Peth, Kessalghat, Chora Chinchola and Nimdela – Ramdegi.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Zones of Tadoba National Park</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are four zones in Tadoba National Park that can be accessed through different gates.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>1. <strong>Moharli Zone:</strong> For a safari ride in this zone you can enter through the Moharli and Khutwanda gates of the Core zone and the Devada, Adegao, Agarzari, Junona &amp; Mamla gates of the Buffer zone.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>2. <strong>Kolara Zone</strong>: To enter this zone you have to book the safari from the Kolara gate of the core zone. You can also enter this zone from Alizanza, Madnapur, Sirkada, Kolara Chauradeo, Palasgaon, and Belara gates of the Buffer zone.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>3. <strong>Navegaon Zone</strong>: This zone can be accessed through the Navegaon gate of the core zone. Buffer zone gates to enter this zone are Navegaon Ramdegi &amp; Nimdela gate.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>4. <strong>Pangadi and Zari zone</strong>: 2 core gates have been made to enter this zone, Pangadi &amp; Zari Gate. You can also book a safari from Pangadi Aswal Chuha, Keslaghat &amp; Zari Peth gate of the buffer zone.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Best Gate of Tadoba National Park</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Although all the gates of Tadoba offer unique landscapes and wildlife viewing opportunities, the Moharli zone is considered the most popular zone for safari due to its higher chance of spotting tigers and other wildlife.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>The most popular gate for safari in Tadoba National Park is the Moharli gate.</strong> This gate is famous among tourists because the black leopard has been frequently spotted here. You can find various accommodation options near this gate. This gate is closest to Telia Lake, many wild animals can be spotted at this lake as they come here to quench their thirst. Moharli has a dense forest area, making it a prime habitat for animals like tigers. So if you\'re looking for the best chance to see wild animals along with tigers in Tadoba, Moharli Gate is the way to go. What are you waiting for? You can book your safari easily by <a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/tadoba-safari-booking\"><strong>Tadoba Online Booking</strong></a> facility.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Published by&nbsp;Sanskriti Goyal</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Which Gate in Tadoba Has a High Chance of Tiger Sightings?','In Tadoba National Park, there are several safari gates from which visitors can enter for wildlife sightings. These gates include 6 gates from the core zone and 12 gates from the buffer zone.','inherit','closed','closed','','12607-revision-v1','','','2024-04-10 07:10:28','2024-04-10 07:10:28','',12607,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12740',0,'revision','',0),(12741,4,'2024-04-10 07:11:20','2024-04-10 07:11:20','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Reaching Tadoba National Park or Tadoba-Andhari Tiger Reserve involves several transportation options depending on your starting point. This park is situated in <strong>Chandrapur district of Maharashtra</strong>. Here\'s a guide on how to reach Tadoba National Park</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>By Air</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The nearest airport to Tadoba National Park is Dr. Babasaheb Ambedkar International Airport in Nagpur. From the airport, you can hire a taxi or take a bus to reach <strong><a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/\">Tadoba National Park</a></strong>. This park is approximately 140 kilometers away from the airport. The journey by bus or taxi from Nagpur Airport to Tadoba National Park typically takes around 4-5 hours, depending on the route and any stops along the way.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>By Train</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The nearest railway station to Tadoba National Park is <strong>Chandrapur Railway Station</strong>, which is about 45 kilometers away. From the railway station, you can hire a taxi or take a bus to reach the park. The journey from Chandrapur Railway Station to Tadoba National Park by taxi or bus typically takes around 1-2 hours, depending on traffic conditions and the route taken.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>By Road</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba National Park is well-connected by road to nearby cities and towns. <strong>Bus services are available </strong>from major cities like Nagpur, Pune, Mumbai, Bangalore, Bhopal, and many more to nearby towns like Chandrapur and Chimur. These buses may be operated by state transport authorities or private companies. It\'s advisable to check the bus schedule and book your tickets in advance, especially during peak seasons. From Chandrapur or Chimur, you can take local transport options such as taxis, auto-rickshaws, or shared jeeps to reach Tadoba National Park.&nbsp; It usually takes 30 to 45 minutes by road to reach the park.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Local Transport</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once you reach the area of Tadoba National Park, you can hire <strong>local taxis, jeeps, or auto-rickshaws </strong>to reach your accommodation or directly to the park entrance gates. Many resorts and lodges near the park offer pick-up and drop-off services for their guests.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It\'s advisable to plan your transportation and consider factors such as distance, travel time, entry timings, safari schedules, and convenience when choosing the best option to reach the Park. There are three main entry points to the Park: <strong>Moharli Gate, Kolara Gate, and Navegaon Gate.</strong> Choose your accommodation and travel options according to the entry gate you have chosen for your safari. Additionally, always check for the latest travel updates and road conditions before starting your journey towards <strong><a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/\">Tadoba National Park.</a></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Published by&nbsp;Sanskriti Goyal </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','How to Reach Tadoba National Park','','inherit','closed','closed','','12614-revision-v1','','','2024-04-10 07:11:20','2024-04-10 07:11:20','',12614,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12741',0,'revision','',0),(12742,4,'2024-04-10 07:11:38','2024-04-10 07:11:38','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Reaching Tadoba National Park or Tadoba-Andhari Tiger Reserve involves several transportation options depending on your starting point. This park is situated in <strong>Chandrapur district of Maharashtra</strong>. Here\'s a guide on how to reach Tadoba National Park</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"20px\"}}} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:20px\"><strong>By Air</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The nearest airport to Tadoba National Park is Dr. Babasaheb Ambedkar International Airport in Nagpur. From the airport, you can hire a taxi or take a bus to reach <strong><a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/\">Tadoba National Park</a></strong>. This park is approximately 140 kilometers away from the airport. The journey by bus or taxi from Nagpur Airport to Tadoba National Park typically takes around 4-5 hours, depending on the route and any stops along the way.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>By Train</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The nearest railway station to Tadoba National Park is <strong>Chandrapur Railway Station</strong>, which is about 45 kilometers away. From the railway station, you can hire a taxi or take a bus to reach the park. The journey from Chandrapur Railway Station to Tadoba National Park by taxi or bus typically takes around 1-2 hours, depending on traffic conditions and the route taken.</p>\n<