u cannot enter the park premises. After your safari you can stay near the park, <strong><a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/hotels-in-tadoba\">Tadoba Hotel Booking</a></strong> can be done on our website.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>8.Tadoba is a protected area and just like many wildlife sanctuaries,&nbsp; Tadoba faces challenges like habitat loss and conflicts between animals and people.&nbsp; The government takes care of this park and they always make conservation efforts to protect the park and its inhabitants.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Overall,this Park is a wonderful place to experience nature and see a wide variety of wildlife. It offers a unique opportunity to observe animals in their natural habitat and learn about conservation efforts in India. Whether you\'re a nature lover, a wildlife enthusiast, a bird watcher or just looking for a peaceful getaway, <strong>Tadoba National Park</strong> has something for everyone.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Published by&nbsp;Sanskriti Goyal</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Facts About Tadoba National Park','','inherit','closed','closed','','12673-revision-v1','','','2024-04-10 07:54:59','2024-04-10 07:54:59','',12673,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12759',0,'revision','',0),(12761,4,'2024-04-10 08:13:35','2024-04-10 08:13:35','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>News Update: A tiger in <a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/\">Tadoba National Park</a> is making headlines after a video of him removing a plastic bottle from a waterhole went viral. The video shows a young tiger picking up a plastic bottle thrown behind by a visitor during a safari.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The tiger, believed to be the offspring of a tigress named Bhanuskhindi, was caught on camera cleaning up the waterhole inside Tadoba National Park. The footage of this incident has been widely shared on social media platforms.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Indian Forest Service officer Susanta Nanda shared the video on X, urging people to be mindful of their trash and not leave plastic waste behind in natural habitats. Sharing the video of the tiger cleaning the water body, Susanta Nanda asked, \"Why should the wild clean the garbage of the (un) civilized?\" and requested, \"Please stop bringing plastics &amp; styrofoams into the wilderness.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Not only this In another post, Susanta Nanda shared that the tiger picked up the plastic bottle and placed it in front of the person recording the video from their safari vehicle. He emphasized that the tiger\'s action delivered a clear message to everyone.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This heartwarming video serves as a reminder of the importance of keeping our wildlife sanctuaries clean and protecting the environment for the animals that call it home.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Video reference - <a href=\"https://x.com/susantananda3/status/1757600133699526701?s=20\">https://x.com/susantananda3/status/1757600133699526701?s=20</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Post reference -&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href=\"https://x.com/susantananda3/status/1757615745113235787?s=20\">https://x.com/susantananda3/status/1757615745113235787?s=20</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Published by&nbsp;Sanskriti Goyal</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Tiger Helps Clean Up Plastic Bottle in Tadoba National Park','','inherit','closed','closed','','12680-revision-v1','','','2024-04-10 08:13:35','2024-04-10 08:13:35','',12680,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12761',0,'revision','',0),(12762,4,'2024-04-10 08:15:30','2024-04-10 08:15:30','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>News Update: A tiger in <a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/\">Tadoba National Park</a> is making headlines after a video of him removing a plastic bottle from a waterhole went viral. The video shows a young tiger picking up a plastic bottle thrown behind by a visitor during a safari.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The tiger, believed to be the offspring of a tigress named Bhanuskhindi, was caught on camera cleaning up the waterhole inside Tadoba National Park. The footage of this incident has been widely shared on social media platforms.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Indian Forest Service officer Susanta Nanda shared the video on X, urging people to be mindful of their trash and not leave plastic waste behind in natural habitats. Sharing the video of the tiger cleaning the water body, Susanta Nanda asked, \"Why should the wild clean the garbage of the (un) civilized?\" and requested, \"Please stop bringing plastics &amp; styrofoams into the wilderness.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Not only this In another post, Susanta Nanda shared that the tiger picked up the plastic bottle and placed it in front of the person recording the video from their safari vehicle. He emphasized that the tiger\'s action delivered a clear message to everyone.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This heartwarming video serves as a reminder of the importance of keeping our wildlife sanctuaries clean and protecting the environment for the animals that call it home.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Video reference - <a href=\"https://x.com/susantananda3/status/1757600133699526701?s=20\">https://x.com/susantananda3/status/1757600133699526701?s=20</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Published by&nbsp;Sanskriti Goyal</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Tiger Helps Clean Up Plastic Bottle in Tadoba National Park','','inherit','closed','closed','','12680-revision-v1','','','2024-04-10 08:15:30','2024-04-10 08:15:30','',12680,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12762',0,'revision','',0),(12763,4,'2024-04-10 08:17:25','2024-04-10 08:17:25','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba Andhari Tiger Reserve or <a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/\">Tadoba National Park</a> is a wild tourist spot, famous among wildlife enthusiasts and nature lovers. This park is located in Maharashtra and is one of the most preferred tiger destinations in India. Here you can enjoy different types of activities like jeep safaris, boat rides, birding, trekking, etc. Here is a list of activities that you can enjoy in and around Tadoba National Park.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":12702,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://tadobapark.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Top-Activities-Around-Tadoba-National-Park-Inner-Image-1024x538.jpg\" alt=\"Top Activities Around Tadoba\" class=\"wp-image-12702\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">1. Visit to Butterfly Garden&nbsp;</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The beautiful butterfly garden is located at the Agarzari village on Chandrapur- Moharli Road near Tadoba National Park. This garden covers a huge area of five acres and it’s a real butterfly world. The butterfly goes through 4 different life stages: egg, larva, Chrysalis, and adult, you can see each life stage of butterflies here. It’s an open-air meadow that has food plants to attract butterflies. Many butterflies from Tadoba visit this place and around 80 species of them, call this place their home. This garden was inaugurated back on February 10th and it was made to educate tourists about butterflies and the importance of every species in the ecosystem. You can get knowledge about different kinds of butterflies after coming here. This garden was made to conserve butterflies but many people try to catch butterflies in their hands, and because of that, a glasshouse is there in the garden to help the visitors watch the butterflies in proximity.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">2. Boat ride in Irai Lake&nbsp;</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Forest Department offers a boat riding facility on the backwaters of Irai Lake. Many bird watchers and photographers like to do this activity as many residents as well as migratory birds can be found near the lake. Birds like heaven Crested Pochard, Grey Heron, Stork Billed Kingfisher, Cotton pygmy goose, etc. can be found with different migratory birds during the winter season. You can enjoy boat riding on Irai Lake from 7:00 AM – 5:00 PM. Just like safari rides, boating is also closed for tourist activity in Tadoba from July to October end because of the monsoon season. Visiting here and doing a boat ride will surely be an amazing experience for Birdwatchers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">3. Try Jeep Safari Ride&nbsp;</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba National Park is a wild place that is famous for its tiger population along with a wide variety of other fauna and flora species. Every year, thousands of people come here to see animals from a closer view. People can do that by going on jeep safari rides. Jeep safari rides are done on gypsies, that go inside the park, it offers chances to see wild animals in their natural habitat. To go on rides inside the park, you have to get permits from forest officials. You can book your permit from <a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/tadoba-safari-booking\">Tadoba Online Safari Booking</a>. These rides are done in different zones of the park at different times so that people can explore the area according to their preferences. People sometimes cannot book rides according to their timing or zone preference because the slots tend to fill up quickly, so it is advised to book them 45 days before your arrival.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">4. Walk into Local Villages</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After a thrilling safari ride in Tadoba, walk towards villages near the park. This park is surrounded by various Gond Tribal villages and you can interact with people, to learn about their culture and beliefs. Tell them about yours and gain knowledge about them. You can spend your time enjoying traditional dance and music performances. Take time to see their handicrafts that are uniquely made. Try local food from the shops in and around the villages. This sharing of culture will help you understand how people and nature are linked.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">5. Ramdegi Waterfalls and Temple&nbsp;</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you’re a devotee and into spirituality, then you must visit Ramdegi Temple. It can be a good break from the busy, city life. You can find peace and calm in the surroundings of this place. If you want to have some fun, click some good pictures, and want to see different types of fishes, birds, and butterflies then a visit to Ramdegi waterfall should be there on your checklist. It’s a beautiful scenic place that is located close to Tadoba National Park.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Published by&nbsp;Sanskriti Goyal </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Top Activities Around Tadoba National Park','Tadoba Andhari Tiger Reserve or Tadoba National Park is a wild tourist spot, famous among wildlife enthusiasts and nature lovers. This park is located in Maharashtra and is one of the most preferred tiger destinations in India','inherit','closed','closed','','12701-revision-v1','','','2024-04-10 08:17:25','2024-04-10 08:17:25','',12701,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12763',0,'revision','',0),(12764,4,'2024-04-10 08:21:05','2024-04-10 08:21:05','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/\">Tadoba National Park</a> which is a wild palace, famous among tourists, especially wildlife enthusiasts, remains closed during the monsoon season because of rainfall. After summer, monsoon takes place from July to mid-October and in that period, tourism activities shut down in the area, but this place becomes live during this time. During monsoon, with shades of green, this jungle becomes alive with a mesmerizing symphony of life. The monsoon season is a scenic time, which brings great transformation in the park after summer, as the rain brings out the beauty of greenery in the area. This time is breeding time for some animals and people cannot disturb them during this season. The park becomes brown and dry because of the heat in summer, but because of the monsoon, it changes to a scenic place for tourism in the upcoming months. Everyone must visit here during this time of the year.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">The Greenery Unfolds</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As the rain drops gently touch the dusty grounds, a miracle happens. From a dry land to a lush green forest, the park transforms completely. The dull land becomes a lively paradise with greenery and beautiful flowering plants. Trees grow tall which makes a beautiful roof of leaves that provides shelter to animals living there. Many herbivore animals find food in this new green world. Everything looks bright, and the air smells fresh and new.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">Wildlife Becomes Happy&nbsp;</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Because of lush green lands, animals start moving. Grazers, like deer, become happy because they get plenty of grass to munch. Big bison called gaur move around like strong castles. Monkeys, like langurs and macaques play around on tall trees, which shows how flora and fauna are connected. Butterflies and other insects sip nectar from flowers and juice from fruits. It’s like a beautiful transformation in nature that people get to see working there.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">The King Comes Out&nbsp;</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With plenty of new plants and food roaming around (prey animals), the real king of the park appears. During monsoon, many prey animals roam in parks for munching and tigers catch them with their amazing skills. As the rain fills up the waterholes, the tigers come out of their hidden homes to drink and show who\'s boss. Their shiny fur covered in raindrops makes them even more mysterious and impressive. With so much greenery around, the tigers can hunt easily and they get more energetic during this time.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">It\'s time for safaris</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When the rainy clouds go away, the Safari season starts in October, and it\'s a big deal. During the early month after the monsoon (from October to December), people who love animals and photographers from everywhere come to see this amazing sight. The park remains lush green with beautiful flowers. Animals are more energetic with plenty of food and migratory birds also visit during winters. Every wildlife enthusiast and nature lover becomes excited, and the safari spots fill up very quickly for rides. Many people pre-book their safaris during monsoons so that they can experience the beauty and wilderness just after the opening of the park. If you want to go, you can book your spot quickly online from Tadoba National Park Online Booking.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Published by&nbsp;Sanskriti Goyal </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Monsoon Beauty of Tadoba National Park','The park becomes brown and dry because of the heat in summer, but because of the monsoon, it changes to a scenic place for tourism in the upcoming months. Everyone must visit here during this time of the year. ','inherit','closed','closed','','12705-revision-v1','','','2024-04-10 08:21:05','2024-04-10 08:21:05','',12705,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12764',0,'revision','',0),(12766,4,'2024-04-10 08:24:50','2024-04-10 08:24:50','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With rich biodiversity and a huge number of tigers, Tadoba National Park is a famous wildlife sanctuary among enthusiasts and nature lovers. To enjoy your rides to the fullest without worrying about safety you have to follow certain rules that will ensure proper safety of humans as well as animals.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">Tadoba National Park</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba National Park is a wild location in Chandrapur district, also known as the biological hotspot of Maharashtra. Apart from tigers, this park is home to leopards, wild pigs, sambar, chital and wild dogs, sloth bears, and a variety of species of birds. Along with these animals, you can find many bamboo and teak trees with other flora species. A safari ride in this park will surely be an amazing experience. This park should be on the visit list of people coming to Maharashtra to spend their holidays. To gain more information and book a safari ride in this amazing park you can visit <strong><a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/\">Tadoba National Park Online Booking</a>.</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Do’s in Tadoba&nbsp;</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>When you book your rides then permits will be given to you to enter the park, do take them with you. Without permits, entry is not allowed in the park.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You should always maintain a safe distance from animals and avoid disturbing them while on your safari.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You should observe the park quietly without making any noise.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You should always follow your guide\'s instructions as they know the park better than you.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>&nbsp;There are designated routes for safaris and nature walks inside the park so you have to enjoy there only.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>&nbsp;Always respect the park’s boundaries and avoid straying into restricted areas.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>If you want to see animals from a closer view, use binoculars or cameras, instead of approaching them.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Try to talk in a lower voice when having a conversation with someone.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Carry a plastic bag to keep your garbage, and then throw it after coming outside in the dustbin.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Read all the rules and regulations before entering the park.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Don\'ts in Tadoba  </h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Don’t try to feed animals as it will disturb their natural habitat and they will start depending on humans.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Don’t feed animals because of safety reasons also.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>If you find any animal cute, don’t try to touch it, as it can be wild.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Don’t use recorders or any sounds inside the park as animals get disturbed by them.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Don’t use flash photography, especially when photographing animals at night.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Smoking and lighting fires are strictly prohibited inside the park.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Don’t pluck flowers or don’t try to take anything from the park as it will disturb the natural life.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Don’t take alcohol inside, as it is strictly prohibited.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Talking non-veg inside the park is not allowed.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Don’t try to get down from the jeep, unless told by your guide.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Conclusion&nbsp;By following these rules and regulations you can have a fun time in Tadoba. If you adhere to these simple do’s and don’ts then surely your safari ride will be thrilling and adventurous in Tadoba National Park. To make your trip more memorable you can choose from our<a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/tadoba-tour-packages\"> tour packages of Tadoba</a> that will allow you to enjoy the best in less time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Published by&nbsp;Sanskriti Goyal </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Essential Do\'s and Don\'ts in Tadoba National Park','With rich biodiversity and a huge number of tigers, Tadoba National Park is a famous wildlife sanctuary among enthusiasts and nature lovers. ','inherit','closed','closed','','12709-revision-v1','','','2024-04-10 08:24:50','2024-04-10 08:24:50','',12709,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12766',0,'revision','',0),(12767,4,'2024-04-10 08:25:53','2024-04-10 08:25:53','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba is one of the oldest national parks in India and it covers a huge area of 1727 sq km, with a huge variety of flora and fauna. This park was designated as a tiger project back in 1996 and is home to over 130 tigers along with various rare animals such as leopards, wild dogs, hyenas, wild boar, sloth bears, and bison. There are also drones in this park which are contributing to the protection of forests and wildlife and also safeguarding the lives of forest field staff and the local community. To see wild animals, you can visit <a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/tadoba-safari-booking\">Tadoba National Park</a> and you can see them by booking a safari ride. But before visiting let me tell you some important stuff that you should take for a safari ride in this park.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>1. ID and Permits -</strong> Permits are written permissions given by authorities in the form of tickets to enter the park. The timings, zone, guest information, etc are written on them. These are required at the entry gate, you cannot enter the park premises without permits. IDs are your identity cards, you have to bring the same IDs about which you have filled in information while taking the permit. It can be a Passport, Voter ID, License, Aadhar&nbsp; Card, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>2. Wear Comfortable Clothes </strong>- If you’re going in summer then it is advised that you should pack lightweight comfortable clothes, it would be best if they have full sleeves so that you can protect yourself from insect bites and sun damage. If you’re coming in winter then choose layering clothing style. Pack your jackets or sweaters for morning and evening rides.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>3. Footwear-</strong> Try to wear comfortable boots or sneakers, ladies keep your heels at home. If you want a comfortable journey without breaking your precious footwear then choose hiking boots over anything.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>4. Hat or Shades -</strong> The temperature is hot and humid during summer in the park, so don’t forget to bring your hat and sunglasses so that you can protect your eyes and face from the sun and it will also give you a nice sighting experience during Jungle Safari.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>5. Keep these</strong> Things Handy - Binoculars are important for sighting animals so that you can see them from a distance, of course, you can find some animals around you but the more sighting the better, right? Cameras are important for taking nice photographs of animals and birds while they are living in their homes.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>6. Protect Yourself -</strong> You should definitely take bug spray and sunscreens with you so that you can protect your skin from bugs and insects of Tadoba-Andhari Tiger Reserve. Sunscreen is important for protection from harmful UV rays, do re-apply it every two hours.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>7. Important Backpack&nbsp;</strong> - Take a backpack in which you can put above mentioned things along with water, snacks, a first aid kit, and any medicine that you’re taking for your health concerns. Try to carry a smaller backpack so that you can enjoy the safari ride.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>8. Power -</strong> Don’t forget to keep your chargers, power backup, and extra batteries with you for your electronic devices like phones and cameras so that you can take some good shots.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Conclusion</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After taking all this stuff, you’re ready to go on a thrilling journey to Tadoba National Park, to book your permits you can visit <a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/\">Tadoba National Park Online Booking</a> and you can gain more information about the park there.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Published by&nbsp;Sanskriti Goyal </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Pack Smart for Tadoba National Park','','inherit','closed','closed','','12711-revision-v1','','','2024-04-10 08:25:53','2024-04-10 08:25:53','',12711,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12767',0,'revision','',0),(12769,4,'2024-04-10 08:35:03','2024-04-10 08:35:03','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba National Park is a nice tourist destination that has many things to offer. This place has recently become one of the most preferred destinations in India. <a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/\">Tadoba Andhari Tiger Reserve</a> is located in the Chandrapur district of Maharashtra and not only animals, but you can find age-old monuments and temples here. With a lot of flora and fauna such as Tigers,&nbsp; leopards, chital, chinkara, langurs, nilgai, barking deer, blue bull, etc. this park is known as the <strong>‘Jewel of Vidarbha’</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Keep your cameras ready to capture beauty as there are a lot of things to explore in and around Tadoba National Park or the Tadoba Andhari Tiger Reserve.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":12732,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://tadobapark.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/fOR-TADOBA-2-IMAGE-INNER-IMAGE-FOR-BLOG-1024x538.jpg\" alt=\"Tadoba Machan watch\" class=\"wp-image-12732\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"20px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:20px\">1. Safari</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Can you tell me the best way to explore the flora and fauna of the park other than the canter or jeep safari? <a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/tadoba-safari-booking\">Jeep safari and Canter safari</a> in Tadoba National Park are the best options for exploring the park. While on your safari rides, you can enjoy spotting the Royal Bengal Tiger, or Indian Leopard, Barking deer, small Indian civet, flying squirrel, fox, jackal, wolf, etc., and the flora species such as Bija tree, Kusum tree, bark tree, bamboo groves, and grasses and so on. If you especially want a tiger sighting experience then book your ride for the Moharli zone as that one is famous among wildlife enthusiasts for prominent tiger sightings.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"20px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:20px\">2. Safari At Night</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This safari has recently been added to Tadoba National Park. Now, you can experience the thrill of the Jungle at Night. This safari is more popular than day safari among wildlife enthusiasts as it offers more thrill. During your safari, you don\'t know which animal can come in front of your jeep out of the blue at night. These safaris are best for experiencing the adventure of being inside a jungle at night. Many animals get active, especially during the night so it\'s the best time to spot those animals.&nbsp; These safaris are action-packed as during your safari you can listen to the wild sounds of animals but you won’t be able to see them from a distance.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"20px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:20px\">3. Machan Watch</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This one is the latest tourist attraction in Tadoba Andheri Tiger Reserve. Machan watch is opened in the Moharli and Palasgaon buffer areas. People can go up by climbing and sit in these machans to spot wild animals from the top. The safaris that you have booked will take you on these machans. Two people can climb on machan with one guide at a time to enjoy panorami0c views with better sighting. People can carry their refreshments at the top but littering is not allowed so keep a plastic bag for disposing of your waste in it so that after the ride you can throw the plastic bag in the dustbin. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"20px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:20px\">4. Village Visits</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can go for nature walks in the buffer zones of Tadoba. There are many villages in the buffer zones of Tadoba Andhari Tiger Reserve and you can visit these areas. These villages are occupied by tribal groups of Gonds, Korkur, Kolams, and Andh, and you can spend time with them, and chat with them with help from a guide. People can go to their work areas and see nice bamboo works of furniture, home decor, baskets, swings, etc. that artisans and craftsmen make.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"20px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:20px\">5. Sevagram</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is a town where Gandhi Ji (father of the nation) has set up an ashram, and he also lived here. This ashram is located at a 2 hours drive from Tadoba National Park and Gandhi Ji lived here from <strong>1936</strong> to his <strong>death in 1948</strong>. You can find artifacts of India’s freedom struggles in this museum. A trip to Sevagram will give you a glimpse of the memories of pre-independent India.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Unforgettable Moments at Tadoba National Park','Tadoba National Park is a nice tourist destination that has many things to offer. This place has recently become one of the most preferred destinations in India. ','inherit','closed','closed','','12727-revision-v1','','','2024-04-10 08:35:03','2024-04-10 08:35:03','',12727,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12769',0,'revision','',0),(12770,4,'2024-04-10 11:54:58','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba National Park is a famous wildlife park located in Maharashtra, India. This park is home to many different species of flora and fauna that are found in huge numbers, which makes it an ideal destination to explore for wildlife and nature lovers. People can explore this place by going on<a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/tadoba-safari-booking\"> Jeep Safaris</a> inside the Park. The park is famous for sightings of tigers and they have become the iconic symbol of the park\'s natural beauty because they represent beauty and strength. In this blog, we will discuss the most famous tigers of Tadoba and also we will tell you why they are famous and what makes them different from others.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">Most Famous Tigers:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Maya: </strong>She is one of the most famous tigers and is popularly known as the Queen of Tadoba. Because of her exceptional hunting skills and fierce nature, she got the title of Queen. She is the daughter of Madhuri, who was a famous tigress warrior who died in 