ri rides.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"20px\"}}} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:20px\">2. Wild Dogs (Dholes)</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The wild dogs that are also popular as Dholes are one of the endangered animals, found in Tadoba National Park. These are one of the top predators and are highly social animals that hunt cooperatively in packs. They are intelligent species that hunt strategically.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"20px\"}}} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:20px\">3. Indian Leopards</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba National Park is like a home to Indian Leopards and they can be found there in good numbers. Many people don’t know about this thing because they are overshadowed by their larger and more famous cousins, tigers.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"20px\"}}} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:20px\">4. Sloth Bears</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba National Park has a forest area that is the best habitat for sloth bears. Sloth bears are shy and they are more active at night. These bears are famous because of their shaggy skin with black furs and also they have a good ability to climb trees.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"20px\"}}} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:20px\">5. Four-horned Antelope&nbsp;</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>They are small and rarely seen antelope species. They have got this name because they have four horns on their head, Tadoba is one of those places where these rarely seen species can be found.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragra