te Step-by-Step Guide to Tadoba Safari Booking','','inherit','closed','closed','','12795-revision-v1','','','2024-04-18 11:31:45','2024-04-18 11:31:45','',12795,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12798',0,'revision','',0),(12799,4,'2024-04-19 12:43:14','2024-04-19 12:43:14','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The famous wild park of Maharashtra, Tadoba National Park is divided into 3 zones for tourism. This park covers a huge area of  625 square kilometers and is famous among people for its thriving population of Bengal tigers. Many tourists like to visit this wild area to see these elusive big cats in their natural habitat. It has so much tiger population that it is one of the premier tiger reserves in India. Beyond Tigers, this park is home to many bird species and different animals along with a wide variety of flora. This rich variety of flora and fauna can be seen in different zones of the park. You can just book your safaris to see them and enjoy the thrill of going deep inside the Jungle. Every zone in Tadoba National Park has its own charm and every zone offers unique experiences. Before <a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/tadoba-safari-booking\"><strong>Tadoba Safari Booking</strong></a>, you should know about the zones so that you can book your ride in the zone of your preference sightings. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">Tadoba Andhari Tiger Reserve: An Introduction</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Before delving into the specifics of each zone, it\'s essential to understand the broader context of Tadoba Andhari Tiger Reserve. This park which was established back in 1995 is called the Pride of Maharashtra. This is the largest and oldest wildlife sanctuary that is noted for protecting and conserving a number of endangered species of Tigers and wild animals. This park is the dream destination of Wildlife enthusiasts and nature lovers, as they get good sightings of animals here.&nbsp; The Tadoba Andhari Tiger Reserve comprises both Tadoba National Park and Andhari Wildlife Sanctuary, together forming a haven for numerous species of flora and fauna. Other than wildlife enthusiasts, people like to come here to spend short holidays of 2 or 3 days. See these <a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/tadoba-tour-packages\"><strong>Tadoba Tour Packages</strong></a> for a nice short trip.&nbsp; Especially those seeking adventure should come here as they can get the excitement and thrill of going inside the jungle and encountering wild animals that may roam freely near the safaris. This park is divided into 3 zones for tourism and every zone offers different opportunities for exploring the park. All zones can be accessed through different gates but they are interconnected. You should consider the information before booking your safari.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:22px\">The Zones of Tadoba National Park</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>1. Moharli Zone:</strong> This is the most popular zone that is located in the southwestern part of Tadoba. This zone can be accessed from 7 gates and it is the best place to spot tigers and other rare species. Tourists mostly visit this zone and tigers are considered as the pride of this area. Visitors can go on jeep safaris roaming inside the jungle in search of animals such as tigers, leopards, sloth bears, and different avian species. Don’t forget that this zone comes under one of the country\'s premium wildlife and biosphere reserves. If you’re specially coming for birding then you can find various birds near the Telia lake that is located in this zone. Tigress Sonam and her cubs dominate the area near Telia Lake, you can spot them if you’re lucky. The famous sighting spots of this zone are Telia Lake, Jamunzora, and Aswalhira. Here you can get good pictures of tigers and other wild animals.&nbsp; The buffer gates for entering this zone are Devada, Junona, Agarzari, Adegao, and Mamla gates.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>2. Kolsa Zone:</strong> This zone is in the southern part of Tadoba and offers a more rugged and remote wilderness experience. Only 6 vehicles are allowed to enter here in each shift, so book your safaris accordingly. In this part of the forest, you can find the shy and elusive species such as the Indian pangolin and the rusty-spotted cat. The gates for entering this zone are the Zari and Pangadi gates. While on your rides you will see spectacular forest scenic beauty and landscapes. Other zones of Tadoba are more famous than this one because tiger sightings are not common here. The buffer gates for entering this zone are Keslaghat, Pangadi, and Zari Peth gates.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>3. Tadoba Zone:</strong> This zone is in the northern part of Tadoba and offers spectacular views of nature along with a wide variety of wildlife. This zone has scenic landscapes and it is one of the best areas to spot tigers roaming in the Jungle. This zone is highly famous among wildlife enthusiasts and photographers who come to Tadoba to watch wildlife close to them. The sighting areas of this zone are Tadoba Lake, Kolara Road, Jamni Lake, and Pandharpauni, animal and bird sightings are most common in these spots. A variety of wildlife can be found here such as leopards, sloth bears, wild dogs, sambar deer, and various species of birds and reptiles. The entry gates for this zone are the Navegaon and Kolara gates. The buffer gates for entering this zone are Madnapur, Alizanza, KolaraChauradeo, Sirkheda, Belara, and Palasgaon gates.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"18px\"}}} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:18px\">How to Reach This Beautiful Park&nbsp;</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This huge park is located in the Chandrapur district of Maharashtra and one can easily reach here from different parts of the country. This park has a good rail, road, and air network.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>By Air:</strong> The nearest airport for which you should book your flights is Dr. Babasaheb Ambedkar International Airport. This airport is just 140 km and will take around 3 hours to reach the park.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>By Rail:</strong> The nearest Railway Station is Chandrapur so book your tickets for that station. The distance between this station and the park is 45 km and it will take around 1 or 11⁄2 hours to cover this distance.&nbsp; This station is well connected with various neighboring cities like Hyderabad, Mumbai, Delhi, Jhansi, and Chennai.&nbsp;<br><strong>By Road:</strong> The nearest bus stop is Chandrapur (45 km) and Chimur (32 km). From there you can find any local transport to reach the park. Tadoba National Park has an excellent road network with well-constructed roads so can come here by your own vehicle or you can find many government and private buses to reach here.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','A Comprehensive Guide to the Zones of Tadoba National Park','The famous wild park of Maharashtra, Tadoba National Park is divided into 3 zones for tourism. This park covers a huge area of  625 square kilometers and is famous among people for its thriving population of Bengal tigers. ','publish','open','open','','a-comprehensive-guide-to-the-zones-of-tadoba-national-park','','','2024-04-19 12:45:03','2024-04-19 12:45:03','',0,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12799',0,'post','',0),(12800,4,'2024-04-19 12:42:08','2024-04-19 12:42:08','','A Comprehensive Guide to the Zones of Tadoba National Park','','inherit','open','closed',''