ack. People are saying it\'s a heartwarming video as the cub can be seen as very happy because of the rain. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During summers, the temperature of Tadoba goes up to 47°C, and because of this many animals are mostly seen near water bodies. Animals go near the water to quench their thirst and play in it. The wild animals of Tadoba who used to spend hours in the water to cool their bodies in summer enjoyed this sudden rain a lot. Because of sudden rain in Tadoba, a sloth bear with a cub is seen taking a walk inside the park. A bear can be seen taking his cub on his back and roaming around the forest.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Piyush Akre and Kanchan Petkar, head of \'Deccan Driftus\' and wildlife researchers shot this video in the Nimdela-Ramdegi buffer zone of the Tadoba National Park. In that video, it can be clearly seen that the bear was roaming inside the park with a cub on its back. Then they saw a water hole on the safari road and they sipped water from it and started their walk again.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>People are loving the cub in this video. He looks very cute and this video is gaining a lot of likes and views over the internet. If you also want to explore the wild yet cute side of Tadoba then a safari in this park is a must. Book your <a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/tadoba-safari-booking\"><strong>Tadoba Safari</strong> </a>now and have fun inside the jungle.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Viral Video: The Cute Sloth Bear of Tadoba During Sudden Rains','Recently a viral video of the Ramdegi Zone of Tadoba National Park is gaining views from Wildlife lovers and people alike.  The video shows a bear having a walk in a beautiful forest with a cub on its back. ','inherit','closed','closed','','12815-revision-v1','','','2024-05-02 11:24:58','2024-05-02 11:24:58','',12815,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12817',0,'revision','',0),(12819,4,'2024-05-03 12:56:00','2024-05-03 12:56:00','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Many people go to different national parks for sightings of Tigers and Leopards. But they don’t know that they can get a chance to see them in one National Park. Tadoba National Park is a famous tourist spot that is home to tigers and leopards along with other animals. You can see tigers along with other animals and birds by going on safari rides in this park. Let me tell you about this in detail.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>What is Tadoba?&nbsp;</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba National Park or you can say Tadoba Andhari Tiger Reserve is one of India\'s 47 project tiger reserves that are in India. It is located in the&nbsp; Chandrapur district of Maharashtra and covers a huge area of 1,727 Sq.km. This area is a mix of park and wildlife sanctuary, the sanctuary was formed in the year 1986 and the park was established in 1995.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This park is known as Tadoba Andhari Tiger Reserve because the word Tadoba is taken from the God \"Tadoba\" or \"Taru,\" which is praised by local tribal people of this region, and \"Andhari\" is taken from the Andhari river flowing in this area. With the river and huge area, this park creates the perfect habitat for wild animals. They get enough food from the flora and they can quench their thirst from the rivers.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This park has rich flora varieties which include Teak, Ain, Bija, Dhauda, Hald, Salai, Semal, Tendu, Beheda, Hirda, Karaya gum, Mahua Madhuca, Arjun, Bamboo, Bheria, Black Plum, and many more. With this much flora, this park is home to animals like Gaur, Nilgai, Sambar, Spotted Deer, Chital, etc. Because of this large animal prey base, this park is home to Tigers, Indian leopards, Sloth bears, dholes, Striped hyenas, Small Indian Civets, Jungle Cats, and many insects and birds.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>About The Safari</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To see the wild animals in their natural habitat people go on jeep or canter safari rides in this huge park. Tadoba National Park remains open for safaris from 15th October to 30th June every year but is closed on Tuesdays. There are four zones available for Safaris - Moharli Zone, Kolara Zone, Navegaon Zone, and Pangadi and Zari Zone. There are many gates to enter these zones for which people can book their Tadoba Safari. To know the full information about the gates of each zone and other related information, you can visit<strong> </strong><a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/tadoba-safari-booking\"><strong>here</strong></a>. To enjoy a safari in these zones you have to do online booking at least 45 days prior to your trip. This will let you choose your preferred zone and also you can choose the safari time according to your preference. The safari is conducted 2 times a day, you can choose a morning safari or an evening safari.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Booking Information</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>- <a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/tadoba-safari-booking\"><strong>Tadoba Online Booking</strong></a> will let you book your safari ride in advance so that you don’t have to get disappointed after reaching there as slots are not available.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>- If you want to book a safari online then you have to provide the complete details of the person who is going to be on the safari like Name, Age, Sex, etc. You also need to give the details of ID cards like Adhar Card, Passport, Pan Card, Voter ID, etc.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-