&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>- After filling in all the details, you just have to clear the payment option and your safari will be confirmed.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> You will be given a confirmation receipt online and you have to download it. Make sure to have a hard copy of that receipt with you when you come for the safari along with original IDs.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Prime Location for Spotting of Tiger and Leopards in India','Many people go to different national parks for sightings of Tigers and Leopards. But they don’t know that they can get a chance to see them in one National Park','inherit','closed','closed','','12819-revision-v1','','','2024-05-03 12:56:00','2024-05-03 12:56:00','',12819,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12821',0,'revision','',0),(12822,4,'2024-05-06 12:40:55','2024-05-06 12:40:55','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tadoba National Park is a wild place that offers thrilling safari rides to go deep inside the forest for spotting tigers and other animals. It does not promise sightings, but if you’re lucky and have patience, you can spot a big cat there. Many people go to this park and most of them come happy with the sightings of big tigers but in some rare chances, some people return unhappy. The one thing that is very important for sighting is patience, without it you won\'t be able to enjoy your ride. You\'ll keep thinking about tiger sightings during the whole ride and you won’t be able to enjoy the thrill of watching other wild animals. So have some patience and enjoy the safari in this huge park. However, here are some easy tips to improve your chances of spotting tigers in <a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/\"><strong>Tadoba National Park</strong></a>.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>1. Select the right zone</strong> - Boost your chances of tiger sightings by heading to the best zone with the maximum number of tiger sightings. If you’re too lazy to do research then you can definitely head towards the Moharli zone of Tadoba National Park. Other good zones would be the Kolara zone or the Navegaon zone. This national park is divided into core and buffer zones and there are different entry gates to enter different zones so choose your zone where you can find various accommodations nearby. If you’re still confused about which zone to choose then choose the zone in which there is a river or pond or something that has water resources so that you can spot animals drinking from them. With some patience and a bit of nice luck, you might spot a big cat in this huge park.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>2. Choose the right season for sightings</strong> - The best time to spot tigers is during summer, they are most active during this time as they roam around in the forest for drinking water again and again. During summer, you must book a safari for a zone in which there is a water stream. Make sure to have sunscreens, water bottles, and other essentials for summer in your backpack. However, if you’re unable to bear the scorching heat then book your safaris from November to February as during winter you can find a tiger chasing prey in the forest. With the right season, the right timing is also important. Try to book your safari for the morning because tigers are more active during that time.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>3. Be attentive inside the forest</strong> - The tiger comes at the top of the food chain in Tadoba and it\'s an apex predator so don’t try to only look for him. Be attentive to what’s happening around you, if you find langurs or sambar deer quickly starts moving, or you find unusual distinct calls made by birds in silence then know that the tiger is going to make his move. Another way of finding the tiger is by spotting his pug marks on the soil by the road and near water bodies. Try to follow those marks to spot him, but do follow the rules and regulations of the forest, and don’t ask the driver to go into prohibited areas.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>4. Choose the right safari</strong> - Tadoba National Park offers two types of vehicles for a safari - a jeep and a canter. It is advised to always pick a jeep because it offers a quiet ride and it can go deep inside the forest. Jeep safaris cost more than canter but they have advantages that offer better sighting opportunities. Canters are bigger in size so they tend to be on the main roads. Which in turn reduces the chances of spotting a tiger,&nbsp; especially if the forest is dense and has no water bodies by the road.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>5. Book Multiple Safaris</strong> - If you’re going to Tadoba, especially for spotting tigers then make sure to book multiple safaris because the wildlife sightings are unpredictable and it totally depends on luck. If you book more safaris then you can spend more time inside the jungle and spending more time inside means that you have more chances to spot wild animals inside the park.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>6. Stay at a nearby accommodation</strong> - If you’re coming to Tadoba and you’re going on safaris 2 times a day then staying at the nearby accommodation would be beneficial. Doing 2 safaris in a day will take around 8 hours to complete and if you choose to stay at a far place then it will take a lot of time to commute to and from your resort. Being late may cost you a sight and also it will tire you a lot so you won’t be able to enjoy the ride.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>7. Choose the right tour agency and guide</strong> - Experience and skill make the difference so choose the best <a href=\"https://tadobapark.com/tadoba-safari-booking\"><strong>Tadoba Online Booking</strong></a> platform so that you will not have any problems during the trip. Also, if you choose the experience agency, their driver and guide will be knowledgeable and know a tiger’s routine and take you to the right place at the right time.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>8. Use Binoculars and Cameras </strong>- When going for a safari then keep binoculars with you to spot tigers, animals, and birds easily from a distance. Binoculars will help you spot wild animals along with small birds and insects from a distance so that you don’t have to go near them. Make sure to have cameras with you for capturing the moment and also the zoom lens will allow you to spot them clearly. Don’t forget to take extra batteries and other essential camera equipment when coming for a nice trip here.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Conclusion&nbsp;</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>These were some simple tips by which your chances of tiger sightings in Tadoba National Park will increase. If you follow these simple and easy tips and remain patient during your ride then you can enhance your chances of spotting tigers in Tadoba and create unforgettable memories of your wildlife adventure. Make your Tadoba Safari Booking now to experience a thrilling safari in Tadoba National Park.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','How to Improve Chances of Spotting Tigers in Tadoba ','Tadoba National Park is a wild place that offers thrilling safari rides to go deep inside the forest for spotting tigers and other animals. ','publish','open','open','','how-to-improve-chances-of-spotting-tigers-in-tadoba','','','2024-05-06 12:43:46','2024-05-06 12:43:46','',0,'https://tadobapark.com/blog/?p=12822',0,'post','',0),(12823,4,'2024-05-06 12:40:19','2024-05-06 12:40:19','','How to Improve Chances of Spotting Tigers in Tadoba','','inherit','open','closed','','how-to-improve-cha