the national parks of India but recently the forest department has allowed night safaris in some national parks. Tadoba is one of the national parks in which people can enjoy a night safari. Night safaris allow us to observe the night wildness of the park. It allows us to observe those animals that are not very active during the day such as rusty-spotted cats, civets, nightjars, and a variety of owls, etc.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"18px\"}}} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:18px\">How is night safari different?&nbsp;</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The night safari experience is a class apart and it gives good vibes and an adventurous experience. Doing a ride inside the park at night has its own charm. Night Safaris lets you enjoy the sights of nocturnal animals. Night safaris are more thrilling because you will be roaming without any light and you don’t know which animal will suddenly appear in front of your gypsies out of the blue.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"18px\"}}} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:18px\">Animals at Night&nbsp;</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Night Safari in Tadoba offers a thrilling experience inside the jungle that everyone should enjoy. It lets you see animals and birds that cannot be seen during the day. Many nocturnal animals become active at night and start their day as it begins to dawn. Some animals have evolved nocturnal habits because of heat avoidance, but some are really nocturnal because of other reasons. Many big animals such as tigers or leopards can be seen chasing prey at night for their dinner.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"18px\"}}} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size:18px\">Do 